## 12. Lambda-Grid Sturm Audit for Degrees 21–30

A compact lambda-grid Sturm audit was performed for the higher-degree range.

Tested deformation values:

\[
\lambda =
0,\ 10^{-6},\ 10^{-5},\ 10^{-4},\ 10^{-3},\ 10^{-2},\ 5\times10^{-2},\ 10^{-1}.
\]

Parameters:

- degrees \(21,\ldots,30\);
- \(n=0,\ldots,20\);
- \(M_k\) computed up to \(k=50\);
- Sturm positive-root counting applied to

\[
Q_{d,n}(y)=P_{d,n}(-y).
\]

Cases per \(\lambda\):

\[
10\times 21=210.
\]

Total cases:

\[
8\times 210=1680.
\]

Result:

\[
1680/1680 \text{ passed}.
\]

Failures:

\[
0.
\]

For every tested \(\lambda\), every degree \(d=21,\ldots,30\), and every \(n=0,\ldots,20\), the polynomial \(Q_{d,n}(y)\) had exactly \(d\) positive real roots.

### Status

The higher-degree Jensen/Sturm pass is stable across the tested positive-\(\lambda\) grid up to \(\lambda=0.1\).
